title: Rwanda Free Trade Zone
description:
Rwanda was ranked the best performing country in the East African region as well as third easiest place to do business in Sub-Saharan Africa by the 2013 World Bank Doing Business Report, thanks to the government's effort to make necessary legal reforms that have been instrumental to this success. 

To further attract Foreign Direct Investment Rwanda has established the "Kigali Special Economic Zone" which is located in Gasabo district 10 minutes drive from Kigali International Airport, city center, the main road connecting all borders and the same zone where the planned train project will pass.
